{
  "texts": [
    "Equally, quantization can convert model weights from floating-point to lower precision to make the inference process lighter.",
    "Knowledge distillation is the process of letting a small model (the so-called student) learn from a great, complex model (the teacher), producing a compact model that does not lose much of the performance.",
    "However, these compression techniques sometimes cause a reduction in the accuracy of the model or the removal of some features, which can affect the system's performance in handling difficult problems.",
    "In some cases, where computational resources are not a limiting factor and accuracy is crucial (e.g., in cloud machine learning services), the potential drawbacks of model compression might offset the advantages.",
    "Thus, AI model compression is relevant for HCAI systems that need to be efficient, but it should be considered more thoroughly for systems that may benefit from increased accuracy."
  ]
}